<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<opml version="2.0">
  <head>
    <title>Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <outline text="Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour" _note="Atomic Learning Graph turns open educational text into a small, offline course. It breaks a hard topic into one-concept lessons, puts prerequisites in a useful order, and keeps each explanation beside the source passage that supports it." ALGKind="showcase" ALGPresentation="styled-one-shot" Color="#264653" Shape="rounded" Badge="point.3.connected.trianglepath.dotted" Width="8" Height="3">
      <outline text="Prototypes" ALGKind="container" Color="#264653" Shape="rounded" Badge="folder">
        <outline text="ALG Tour Step" IsPrototype="true" ALGKind="prototype" Color="#E9C46A" Shape="rounded" Badge="book" Width="5" Height="2.5"/>
        <outline text="ALG Tour Goal" IsPrototype="true" ALGKind="prototype" Color="#E76F51" Shape="rounded" Badge="star" Width="5" Height="2.5"/>
        <outline text="ALG Tour Guide" IsPrototype="true" ALGKind="prototype" Color="#8E7DBE" Shape="rounded" Badge="info.circle" Width="5" Height="2.5"/>
      </outline>
      <outline text="Start Here" _note="A five-step tour of Atomic Learning&#10;&#10;Atomic Learning Graph turns open educational text into a small, offline course. It breaks a hard topic into one-concept lessons, puts prerequisites in a useful order, and keeps each explanation beside the source passage that supports it.&#10;&#10;Import this OPML once, then open Steps in Map view and follow the next links from left to right. This small map is both the product tutorial and the presentation check for the Tinderbox exporter." ALGKind="guide" Prototype="ALG Tour Guide" Color="#8E7DBE" Shape="rounded" Badge="info.circle" Width="7" Height="3" Xpos="0" Ypos="0" ALGXpos="0" ALGYpos="0" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;$Rule=&quot;&quot;}"/>
      <outline text="Steps" ALGKind="container" Color="#264653" Shape="rounded" Badge="folder">
        <outline text="1. Choose a goal" _note="Begin with something specific that you want to understand.&#10;&#10;A clear destination keeps the course focused. Atomic Learning works backward from that goal to find the ideas you need first.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Name one topic that currently feels too large or tangled to learn all at once.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md -- The whole project, steps 1 and 2" ALGExactText="Begin with something specific that you want to understand.&#10;&#10;A clear destination keeps the course focused. Atomic Learning works backward from that goal to find the ideas you need first.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Name one topic that currently feels too large or tangled to learn all at once.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md — The whole project, steps 1 and 2" ALGKind="guide-step" ALGGuideId="choose-a-goal" ALGStep="1" Prototype="ALG Tour Step" Color="#E9C46A" Shape="rounded" Badge="book" Width="5" Height="2.5" Xpos="2" Ypos="5" ALGXpos="2" ALGYpos="5" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;linkTo(find($ALGGuideId==&quot;follow-the-path&quot;),&quot;next&quot;);$Rule=&quot;&quot;}" DisplayedAttributes="ALGStep;ALGGuideId"/>
        <outline text="2. Follow the path" _note="Learn prerequisites before the ideas that depend on them.&#10;&#10;The graph turns relationships into an ordered route. You can see where you are going and why an earlier idea belongs before a later one.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Start at the first item in the map, outline, note list, or deck supplied by your app.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;src/graph/path.ts -- deterministic prerequisite walk" ALGExactText="Learn prerequisites before the ideas that depend on them.&#10;&#10;The graph turns relationships into an ordered route. You can see where you are going and why an earlier idea belongs before a later one.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Start at the first item in the map, outline, note list, or deck supplied by your app.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;src/graph/path.ts — deterministic prerequisite walk" ALGKind="guide-step" ALGGuideId="follow-the-path" ALGStep="2" Prototype="ALG Tour Step" Color="#E9C46A" Shape="rounded" Badge="book" Width="5" Height="2.5" Xpos="8.2" Ypos="8.5" ALGXpos="8.2" ALGYpos="8.5" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;linkTo(find($ALGGuideId==&quot;learn-one-idea&quot;),&quot;next&quot;);$Rule=&quot;&quot;}" DisplayedAttributes="ALGStep;ALGGuideId"/>
        <outline text="3. Learn one idea" _note="Each stop explains one concept in plain language.&#10;&#10;Small lessons reduce the amount you must hold in mind at once. If a lesson feels too hard, step back to its prerequisite instead of pushing through a wall of text.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Read one lesson, then explain its single idea in your own words.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md -- Atomic steps and prerequisite scaffolding" ALGExactText="Each stop explains one concept in plain language.&#10;&#10;Small lessons reduce the amount you must hold in mind at once. If a lesson feels too hard, step back to its prerequisite instead of pushing through a wall of text.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Read one lesson, then explain its single idea in your own words.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md — Atomic steps and prerequisite scaffolding" ALGKind="guide-step" ALGGuideId="learn-one-idea" ALGStep="3" Prototype="ALG Tour Step" Color="#E9C46A" Shape="rounded" Badge="book" Width="5" Height="2.5" Xpos="14.4" Ypos="5" ALGXpos="14.4" ALGYpos="5" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;linkTo(find($ALGGuideId==&quot;check-the-receipt&quot;),&quot;next&quot;);$Rule=&quot;&quot;}" DisplayedAttributes="ALGStep;ALGGuideId"/>
        <outline text="4. Check the receipt" _note="Every explanation stays close to the source passage that supports it.&#10;&#10;You do not have to trust a smooth explanation just because it sounds confident. Open the source receipt and compare the lesson with the original words.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Challenge one explanation by reading the exact quoted passage beside it.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;src/graph/invariants.ts -- quote-primary provenance checks" ALGExactText="Every explanation stays close to the source passage that supports it.&#10;&#10;You do not have to trust a smooth explanation just because it sounds confident. Open the source receipt and compare the lesson with the original words.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Challenge one explanation by reading the exact quoted passage beside it.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;src/graph/invariants.ts — quote-primary provenance checks" ALGKind="guide-step" ALGGuideId="check-the-receipt" ALGStep="4" Prototype="ALG Tour Step" Color="#E9C46A" Shape="rounded" Badge="book" Width="5" Height="2.5" Xpos="20.6" Ypos="8.5" ALGXpos="20.6" ALGYpos="8.5" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;linkTo(find($ALGGuideId==&quot;take-it-with-you&quot;),&quot;next&quot;);$Rule=&quot;&quot;}" DisplayedAttributes="ALGStep;ALGGuideId"/>
        <outline text="5. Take it with you" _note="Use the learning tool you already like.&#10;&#10;The same course can become an Obsidian vault, org-roam file, Tinderbox map, Anki deck, plain Markdown, or an LLM-readable guide. The graph stays the authority; each export is an opinionated presentation for its destination.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Open this showcase in another supported app and compare how the same ideas travel.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md -- What ships beyond the reader" ALGExactText="Use the learning tool you already like.&#10;&#10;The same course can become an Obsidian vault, org-roam file, Tinderbox map, Anki deck, plain Markdown, or an LLM-readable guide. The graph stays the authority; each export is an opinionated presentation for its destination.&#10;&#10;Try it&#10;Open this showcase in another supported app and compare how the same ideas travel.&#10;&#10;Project evidence&#10;README.md — What ships beyond the reader" ALGKind="guide-step" ALGGuideId="take-it-with-you" ALGStep="5" Prototype="ALG Tour Goal" Color="#E76F51" Shape="rounded" Badge="star" Width="5" Height="2.5" Xpos="26.8" Ypos="5" ALGXpos="26.8" ALGYpos="5" Rule="if($ChildCount(&quot;/Atomic Learning Graph - Quick Tour/Steps&quot;)==5){$Xpos=$ALGXpos;$Ypos=$ALGYpos;$Rule=&quot;&quot;}" DisplayedAttributes="ALGStep;ALGGuideId"/>
      </outline>
    </outline>
  </body>
</opml>
